<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Introduction">Introduction</span></h1>
<p>Welcome to the wiki of <b>Miracles of Human Language</b>. This is a collaborative effort of the students of this course. You are invited to contribute to this wiki by:  </p>
<ul>
<ul><li>sharing notes, mindmaps etc
</li><li>explaining difficult concepts
</li><li>correcting spelling and grammar
</li><li>adding (links to) relevant resources, blogs etc.
</li><li>anything else you think is helpful to your fellow students
</li></ul>
</ul>
<p><i>If you need help with how to add things to the wiki you can use the excellent <a href="/wiki/index.php/Markdown_guide" title="Markdown guide">Markdown guide</a> of Coursera.</i></p>
<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Recommended_videos">Recommended videos</span></h1>
<p>These are videos recommended by students. </p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4VILAGHVCs">5 Reasons: David Crystal on "Doing Linguistics"</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jF9qTJD25Ig">Basic Segments of Speech - Consonants</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL230527180E17E9AC">27 Videos on Morphology and Syntax by the Virtual Linguistics Campus</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLRIMXVU7SGRJnARkQhb6LO8KOi5rQf2Qn">10 Micro-Lecture Videos on Semantics by the Virtual Linguistics Campus</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLRIMXVU7SGRJF8gxD70oZPBoFAYxGs4QL">14 Videos on Semantics by the Virtual Linguistics Campus</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.floatinguniversity.com/lectures-pinker">Linguistics as a Window to Understanding the Brain</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B02Kh-DLnkc">Lenguaje, lengua y habla</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aMb7wNTCE3k">Introducción a fonética y fonología</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s9shPouRWCs">Language. CrashCourse</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VAK_ZF6JYTs">El origen del lenguaje (Capítulo REDES 435)</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XdP_dtBvtQo">3 Ideas equivocadas en el lenguaje</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/mark_pagel_how_language_transformed_humanity">How language transformed humanity</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/steven_pinker_on_language_and_thought">What our language habits reveal</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/patricia_kuhl_the_linguistic_genius_of_babies">The linguistic genius of babies</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/keith_chen_could_your_language_affect_your_ability_to_save_money">Could your language affect your ability to save money?</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/john_mcwhorter_txtng_is_killing_language_jk">Txtng is killing language. JK!!!</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/ajit_narayanan_a_word_game_to_communicate_in_any_language">A word game to communicate in any language</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/rajesh_rao_computing_a_rosetta_stone_for_the_indus_script">A Rosetta Stone for a lost language</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/patricia_ryan_ideas_in_all_languages_not_just_english">Don't insist on English!</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/suzanne_talhouk_don_t_kill_your_language">Don't kill your language</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/terry_moore_why_is_x_the_unknown">Why is "X" the unknown</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rYuPFpckHUc">History and Geography of Languages</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RgvmKfvCwps">Theories of Language and Cognition</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RRGwdfQV8kU">Theories of Language Development (Nativist, Learning, Interactionist)</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lBqShvm4QRA">Language and the brain: Aphasia and split-brain patients</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P-xLbPsYdv0">What is Aphasia?</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wDnh6xupkWM">Afasia. Universidad de Concepción</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1aplTvEQ6ew">Expressive aphasia</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PWwPwWs90H0">Come nasce una lingua</a></p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5wHbIWH_NGc">Mongolian Throat Singing</a></p>
<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Recommended_books">Recommended books</span></h1>
<p>These are books recommended by students. </p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/Introduction-Language-Victoria-Fromkin/dp/1133310680/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1428019043&amp;sr=8-3&amp;keywords=fromkin"><em>An Introduction to Language</em></a> - Dr. Victoria Fromkin</p>
<p>-<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.indiana.edu/~hlw/book.html">How Language Works (edition 3.0) by Michael Gasser</a>   Free online introductory linguistics textbook. </p>
<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Key_Concepts">Key Concepts</span></h1>
<p>On these pages, key concepts for the course and for linguistics can be explained and explored in a more structured way than in the Discussion Forums.</p>
